# Terraform Conventions

## File Layout
- `versions.tf` - required Terraform/provider versions
- `backend.tf` - remote state config
- `providers.tf` - provider config with `default_tags`
- `main.tf` - locals and shared data sources
- `variables.tf` - all input variables with validation
- `outputs.tf` - outputs for GitHub Actions integration
- Resource files named by concern: `s3.tf`, `cloudfront.tf`, `r53.tf`, `lambda.tf`, `dynamo.tf`, `secrets.tf`, `gha.tf`, `budget.tf`

## Naming
- Resource names use `${var.todd_name}-${local.environment}` prefix
- Locals for derived values (e.g., `local.site_domain`, `local.environment`)
- No hardcoded names; use locals or variables

## IAM
- Enumerate specific actions; never use `service:*`
- Use `data.aws_iam_policy_document` for policies
- Scope `resources` to specific ARNs where possible

## Architecture Diagram
- Maintained in `architecture.drawio` at repo root
- Export to PNG via: `/opt/homebrew/bin/drawio --export --format png --output architecture.png architecture.drawio`
